I mean, who better
to inoculate the company

14:04.522 --> 14:06.622
when the story breaks
than a queer black woman.

14:06.658 --> 14:09.292
- Yeah.
- I see.

14:09.327 --> 14:11.394
Sorry.

14:14.499 --> 14:18.267
So they want you to be
their black bi bandaid?

14:18.303 --> 14:20.336
To cover up their racist,
homophobic boo-boo.

14:20.371 --> 14:21.604
What are you gonna do?

14:21.639 --> 14:23.472
Sure as hell not gonna be their mascot.

14:26.277 --> 14:27.995
- Oliver?
- Who else?

14:27.996 --> 14:28.996
_

14:30.381 --> 14:33.316
Hey, Oliver, I just got your text.

14:33.351 --> 14:35.551
The only thing is when
you told me to nod,

14:35.587 --> 14:38.354
I just... I thought
that meant say yes, so...

14:39.490 --> 14:41.624
I know.

14:41.659 --> 14:44.460
I know, okay, well, bonsoir.

14:47.365 --> 14:50.366
Long-distance,
pissed-off Oliver is so much worse

14:50.401 --> 14:52.235
than up-close-and-personal,
pissed-off Oliver.

14:52.270 --> 14:54.337
He just found I want
to cut the budget for

14:54.372 --> 14:56.170
the "Divas and Dive" shoot
to make our new number.

14:56.205 --> 14:57.473
I thought that was a good thing.

14:57.508 --> 14:59.675
Well, the problem is now
we can't afford the location,

14:59.711 --> 15:02.245
and shooting at Chad's
was the only reason

15:02.280 --> 15:03.479
Oliver wanted to do the spread.

15:03.514 --> 15:06.482
So basically it's my
first budget meeting...

15:07.018 --> 15:08.384
and I blew it.

15:08.419 --> 15:12.455
Hey, so who wants to go on a field trip?

15:12.490 --> 15:14.423
- Where are we going?
- Hecksher playground.

15:14.459 --> 15:16.292
- I've been juicing.
- Thank you.

15:16.327 --> 15:18.494
I found a play group of
20-something-year-old moms

15:18.529 --> 15:20.329
and their kids.

15:20.365 --> 15:22.331
Cool.

15:22.367 --> 15:24.267
Okay, are you gonna talk to some moms?

15:24.302 --> 15:25.534
'Cause I have to go
back to the office soon.

15:25.570 --> 15:27.503
I just... I want to watch
for a little longer.

15:27.538 --> 15:30.239
It's like Margaret Mead
found a new tribe.

15:30.275 --> 15:31.813
Yeah, breeders.

15:32.243 --> 15:35.645
Okay, I'm just trying to see
if I can picture myself here.

15:36.322 --> 15:38.414
Aren't you guys curious?

15:38.449 --> 15:42.285
No, not really, but then again
I'm pretty sure I don't want kids, so...

15:42.320 --> 15:44.253
Why not?

15:44.289 --> 15:46.555
I don't know, first of all,
environmental reasons.

15:46.591 --> 15:49.225
There are already too many
of us and too few resources.

15:49.260 --> 15:52.428
Yeah, I do, but I think
it's cause my mom sucked.

15:53.431 --> 15:55.698
You know, I'd love
the opportunity to do better.

15:55.733 --> 15:59.535
Give my kid or kids the
childhood I never had.

16:01.372 --> 16:05.241
I'm not seeing the allure
of being a human Kleenex.

16:05.276 --> 16:07.276
Okay, I'm going in.

16:07.312 --> 16:09.412
- Excuse me, hi.
- Hi.

16:10.310 --> 16:12.448
I'm a writer for "Scarlet" magazine,

16:12.483 --> 16:16.252
and I'm doing a story on
20-something-year-old moms

16:16.287 --> 16:17.553
and I was wondering if I could talk

16:17.588 --> 16:19.488
- to you for a few minutes?
- Sure.

16:19.524 --> 16:22.191
- She's beautiful.
- Thank you.

16:22.226 --> 16:24.293
I work as a waitress at night

16:24.329 --> 16:26.329
so I have more time
for Jacob during the day.

16:26.364 --> 16:30.366
But, not gonna lie,
I'm tired every minute

16:30.401 --> 16:32.668
of every day.

16:32.704 --> 16:35.338
But then I look at his sweet face,

16:35.373 --> 16:37.306
and I know it's all worth it.

16:37.342 --> 16:39.642
How has parenthood
affected your relationship?

16:39.677 --> 16:42.278
My husband and I have
to work at it more.

16:42.313 --> 16:45.214
So we make sure to have at least
two date nights a month.

16:45.249 --> 16:46.515
How do you juggle it all?

16:46.551 --> 16:48.351
My mom.

16:48.386 --> 16:50.586
I couldn't do it without her.

16:50.621 --> 16:52.688
She takes the kids on our date nights

16:52.724 --> 16:54.623
and takes them on the
weekends whenever she can

16:54.659 --> 16:56.292
so I can catch up on some work.

16:56.327 --> 16:57.426
Mama! Help me.

16:57.462 --> 16:58.627
Could you just hold him for a sec?

16:58.663 --> 17:00.629
I have to go catch Tilly.

17:00.665 --> 17:04.532
I'm coming, Tilly.

17:04.569 --> 17:05.458
Hey, Jane!

17:05.503 --> 17:08.570
- Jane, come over here!
- This is so much fun!

17:20.599 --> 17:23.733
_

17:31.083 --> 17:32.743
Wanna go out for dinner?

17:33.785 --> 17:34.679
I guess.

17:36.174 --> 17:38.583
- Italian or Chinese?
- I don't know.

17:38.618 --> 17:41.319
Well, how about Burgers and Brews?

17:41.354 --> 17:43.487
Or Pauly G's or we could
try that new place...

17:43.523 --> 17:44.789
Maybe I don't want to have to choose.

17:44.824 --> 17:47.325
Maybe I don't know what I want.

17:51.531 --> 17:55.633
Are you still feeling nauseous
from the morning-after pill?

17:55.668 --> 17:57.435
No, I'm just...

17:57.470 --> 17:59.403
I'm just really stressed
about this article.

18:00.473 --> 18:02.506
What are you writing about?

18:02.542 --> 18:04.575
Just "Scarlet" stuff.

18:04.611 --> 18:06.444
Totally get it.

18:06.479 --> 18:08.412
I'll leave you alone.

18:08.448 --> 18:10.514
I'm sorry, it's just...

18:10.550 --> 18:14.685
writer's block and surging hormones
are not a great combo.

18:19.392 --> 18:20.591
If you do have a breakthrough,

18:20.627 --> 18:22.660
I'm not working
till tomorrow afternoon, so...

18:22.695 --> 18:24.562
Okay.

18:27.634 --> 18:30.501
- Bye.
- Bye.

18:37.510 --> 18:39.410
Hello, Jacqueline.

18:39.445 --> 18:40.645
- Oh, hi, Sutton.
- Hi.

18:40.680 --> 18:42.580
Is this a really bad time?

18:42.615 --> 18:45.483
Well, admittedly eyebrow
threading is never a good time.

18:46.013 --> 18:48.319
What can I help you with?

18:48.354 --> 18:50.321
Remember when I said that
the fashion department

18:50.356 --> 18:53.370
could cut 10% of their budget
for next month's issue?

18:53.405 --> 18:55.559
I do.

18:55.595 --> 18:59.664
Turns out we can't cut as
much as I thought we could.

18:59.699 --> 19:02.633
So I just need a little bit more money

19:02.669 --> 19:05.703
to make the "Divas and Dives"
shoot tomorrow work.

19:05.738 --> 19:07.705
Yeah, see, the problem, Sutton,

19:07.740 --> 19:09.573
is that the budget is already locked,

19:09.609 --> 19:12.410
and the time to ask for
more money would have been

19:12.445 --> 19:13.611
at yesterday's meeting,
which is why we had,

19:13.646 --> 19:15.479
you know, the meeting.

19:15.515 --> 19:17.314
Of course.

19:17.350 --> 19:18.616
It's just Oliver...

19:18.651 --> 19:20.484
Yeah, Oliver always wants the moon,

19:20.520 --> 19:23.487
and, you know, you just
don't always get the moon so...

19:23.523 --> 19:25.656
so what else can you give him?

19:31.531 --> 19:33.698
I can't write this.

19:38.671 --> 19:42.473
You really have that much
to say about Meghan Markle?

19:43.302 --> 19:45.743
Her marriage to Prince Harry made
a strong progressive statement.

19:45.778 --> 19:48.579
They even had eco-friendly
flowers in their ceremony.

19:48.614 --> 19:50.381
Good for them.

19:50.416 --> 19:53.417
How is the
"Babies are the new Bling" coming?

19:53.453 --> 19:55.786
It's coming.

19:55.822 --> 19:58.322
So far all labor, no baby.

19:59.726 --> 20:02.626
They only want me so
that then when their CEO

20:02.662 --> 20:04.428
is ousted as a racist homophobe,

20:04.464 --> 20:05.629
he can point to me and say,

20:05.665 --> 20:08.666
"Oh, look, some of my best spokespeople
are black lesbians."

20:08.701 --> 20:10.701
When I was negotiating the
product integration deal,

20:10.737 --> 20:12.570
I had no idea.

20:12.605 --> 20:15.740
You know, their image
was so politically correct.

20:15.775 --> 20:17.775
Okay, so can we just walk away?

20:17.810 --> 20:20.478
I've been looking over your
contract for a way out,

20:20.513 --> 20:22.379
a morality clause or
something like that,

20:22.415 --> 20:23.681
but there's nothing.

20:23.716 --> 20:25.683
What are they going
to do if I just refuse

20:25.718 --> 20:27.618
to post an Instagram story?

20:27.653 --> 20:29.553
For starters, they could sue us
for breach of contract.

20:29.589 --> 20:31.689
Which would be incredible
expensive for Safford

20:31.724 --> 20:33.758
and a legal nightmare
for the two of you.

20:33.793 --> 20:36.694
I'm so sorry, Kat.

20:36.729 --> 20:38.629
<i>You really think Sutton's
gonna get this place for free?</i>

20:38.664 --> 20:41.398
<i>I hope so. She really needs it
for this photo shoot.</i>

20:41.434 --> 20:43.701
Oh, well, she's smiling.
That's a good sign.

20:43.736 --> 20:45.770
Yeah, but, see, her arms are crossed.

20:45.805 --> 20:47.772
That's not really,
"You can have your photo shoot

20:47.807 --> 20:50.474
here for free," kind of body language.

20:50.510 --> 20:52.843
Oh, it looks like she's
complimenting the place.

20:52.879 --> 20:54.812
Wow, she's pulling out all the stops.

20:54.847 --> 20:56.547
And how are you?

20:56.582 --> 20:58.783
Are you thinking about
thinking about kids?

20:58.818 --> 21:01.719
No, because every time
I start to think about it,

21:01.754 --> 21:04.688
I wind up feeling sick
and having a panic attack

21:04.724 --> 21:06.624
and I just don't know
how to get past it.

21:06.659 --> 21:08.325
What about you?

21:08.361 --> 21:09.660
Have you figured out
what you're gonna do

21:09.695 --> 21:11.532
- about the Whole Spa thing?
- No.

21:11.632 --> 21:15.466
I have to post my first
Instagram story tomorrow

21:15.501 --> 21:18.402
and I'm still trying to figure
out how I can get out of it.

21:18.437 --> 21:20.371
But right now the best idea I have

21:20.406 --> 21:22.573
is to just bury it in basic hashtags.

21:22.608 --> 21:25.376
Ooh. The basic hashtag trick.

21:25.411 --> 21:26.677
It's a good one.

21:26.712 --> 21:28.712
- Hi, so?
- What's up?

21:28.748 --> 21:30.781
No.

21:32.485 --> 21:33.818
She said they can't afford
to shut the place down

21:33.853 --> 21:36.720
for the shoot even if it's
only for a couple of hours.

21:40.593 --> 21:43.427
Why does Oliver have to have it here?

21:43.462 --> 21:47.565
You know, he bought his first beer here
when he moved to the city.

21:47.600 --> 21:50.401
So the whole shoot is kind
of inspired by this place.

21:50.436 --> 21:52.436
I mean, look at it. It's...

21:52.471 --> 21:54.805
It's like a movie set.

21:58.845 --> 22:00.744
A set.

22:07.486 --> 22:10.321
I use Whole Spa clean wipes
in the middle of the day

22:10.356 --> 22:11.755
because it's a great pick me up.

22:11.791 --> 22:14.792
My skin feels soft,
hydrated, and most of all

22:14.827 --> 22:16.727
I feel like a damn hypocrite.

22:16.762 --> 22:18.329
Okay.

22:18.364 --> 22:20.397
I don't think that it's in your DNA

22:20.433 --> 22:22.566
to do this without calling them out.

22:22.602 --> 22:24.702
Nope. It's not.

22:26.706 --> 22:30.574
But, you know, they did say
that they wanted

22:30.610 --> 22:34.445
that edgy Kat Edison sensibility, so...

22:34.480 --> 22:36.380
maybe I should give them just that?

22:40.265 --> 22:42.652
I think I would rather save the close-up

22:42.687 --> 22:46.656
of the Neon Geode lips until after
the edible essential oil section.

22:46.691 --> 22:48.524
Jane, do you have a sec?

22:48.560 --> 22:51.527
Also, do we have another
photo of Michael B. Jordan?

22:51.563 --> 22:53.429
He is just so beautiful;

22:53.465 --> 22:55.365
everybody's gonna think he's CGI.

22:55.400 --> 22:57.367
We are putting Blake Lively
and her two daughters

22:57.402 --> 22:59.669
on the cover, and your piece
is gonna be the featured story.

22:59.704 --> 23:01.637
That's great.

23:01.673 --> 23:03.373
So when do I get to
see your rough draft?

23:03.726 --> 23:06.776
It's just taking me a little longer
than I thought it would.

23:06.811 --> 23:10.546
You having trouble finding mothers
who are wanting to go on the record?

23:10.582 --> 23:12.548
No, no, that's... that's not it.

23:12.584 --> 23:14.584
Well, if you're finding that

23:14.619 --> 23:16.686
focusing on the trendy
aspect of young motherhood

23:16.721 --> 23:18.621
is... is slowing you down,
then you can just throw out

23:18.656 --> 23:20.423
the babies as accessory angle.

23:20.458 --> 23:23.426
I mean, maybe something
about fourth-wave feminists

23:23.461 --> 23:25.495
who are trying to have it all sooner.

23:25.530 --> 23:27.630
Something that explores
how and why young women

23:27.665 --> 23:29.532
just hitting adulthood
would want to take on

23:29.567 --> 23:31.701
this kind of responsibility.

23:31.736 --> 23:33.536
- Right?
- Yeah.

23:33.571 --> 23:36.472
That is really interesting.
I'll explore that angle.

23:36.508 --> 23:38.641
Great. Well, I can't wait to read it.

23:40.412 --> 23:42.545
Oh, well, this is looking a lot better.

24:00.765 --> 24:03.299
Okay, bottom line is
if I'm going to recreate

24:03.334 --> 24:04.700
Chad's in the Scarlet photo studio

24:04.736 --> 24:07.570
I have $233 for set dec and props.

24:07.605 --> 24:09.405
Yeah, that's almost impossible.

24:09.441 --> 24:12.775
Yes, but not if you grew up
shopping at flea markets.

24:13.608 --> 24:14.677
Don't be afraid to haggle.

24:14.712 --> 24:16.712
We need 30 black and
white framed photos...

24:16.748 --> 24:18.481
ideally New York-y stuff...

24:18.516 --> 24:19.940
- three clocks.
- Do they have to work?

24:20.018 --> 24:22.418
They don't because the
ones at Chad's are broken.

24:22.454 --> 24:24.320
A large screen TV, a chalkboard,

24:24.355 --> 24:25.588
darts, dartboard,

24:25.623 --> 24:27.356
some old maps, sofa and chairs.

24:27.392 --> 24:29.525
- All for under 233?
- 218, actually.

24:29.561 --> 24:30.726
We need money for a
cab back into the city.

24:30.762 --> 24:33.563
Thank you guys so much for doing this.

24:33.598 --> 24:35.765
No problem, just be ready to make

24:35.800 --> 24:37.600
me one of those smoothies when
Jacqueline gives me her whole

24:37.635 --> 24:40.369
"You haven't handed in your piece"
face tomorrow.

24:40.405 --> 24:41.804
I'm on it. Ready?

24:41.840 --> 24:43.573
It's just shopping, right?

24:43.608 --> 24:45.708
Except we're buying stuff nobody wants
with money we don't have.

24:45.743 --> 24:47.410
Exactly.

24:47.445 --> 24:48.711
Go team.

24:51.483 --> 24:53.549
- 15!
- I'll give you 10.

24:53.585 --> 24:55.651
Gimme the 10.

24:55.687 --> 24:57.687
Thank you.

24:57.722 --> 24:59.655
How much is the TV?

25:01.326 --> 25:02.625
- Is that a character?
- Pirate.

25:02.660 --> 25:04.727
10? Here.

25:04.762 --> 25:06.596
Sweet, thank you.

25:06.631 --> 25:08.297
I'll take this too.

25:09.501 --> 25:11.334
Thank you so much. You're a doll.

25:19.511 --> 25:22.345
Oh.

25:27.519 --> 25:30.353
Okay, neon sign. Check.

25:30.388 --> 25:32.788
Photo of Bella Abzug. Check.

25:32.824 --> 25:34.657
- Think we did it.
- Yep.

25:34.692 --> 25:36.526
Uber truck is three minutes away.

25:36.561 --> 25:38.594
So that means we should be
unloading at "Scarlet"

25:38.630 --> 25:40.530
in, like, half an hour.

25:40.565 --> 25:41.764
Oh, we do have to make a pit stop.

25:41.799 --> 25:43.332
- What?
- Yeah.

25:43.368 --> 25:44.534
I thought we got everything?

25:44.569 --> 25:46.602
Almost everything.

25:48.706 --> 25:52.675
There has to be a better way to get
the plastic cups from Chad's.

25:52.710 --> 25:55.411
Eh, not for free.

25:56.614 --> 25:58.414
Jackpot!

26:03.017 --> 26:04.520
<i>I am exhausted.</i>

26:04.556 --> 26:06.522
<i>That's what happens
when you work all night.</i>

26:06.558 --> 26:08.457
On the upside, you did it.

26:08.493 --> 26:11.460
Well, let's see what Oliver
has to say from Paris

26:11.496 --> 26:13.529
once he gets the photos
I'm about to send him.

26:13.565 --> 26:15.364
He's gonna love it.

26:15.400 --> 26:16.666
Come on, we got to go.

26:16.701 --> 26:18.668
We smell a little too
dumpster for my taste.

26:18.703 --> 26:20.536
Oh.

26:20.572 --> 26:23.506
See, the thing is,
is you guys smell like dumpster,

26:23.541 --> 26:26.375
I smell like roses.

26:26.704 --> 26:27.677
No, you don't.

26:27.712 --> 26:29.412
- What?
- She's right.

26:29.447 --> 26:30.546
- You don't.
- You stank.

26:30.582 --> 26:33.382
I promise. I would know.

26:36.487 --> 26:39.455
So you're not even bothering
getting dressed at home anymore?

26:39.490 --> 26:41.791
Oh, they were helping me get ready for
the "Divas and Dives" shoot all night.

26:41.826 --> 26:43.526
Won't say a word.

26:43.561 --> 26:44.755
You're not the only ones
who've had to borrow

26:44.763 --> 26:47.463
an Eliza J maxi dress in
a desperate time of need.

26:49.567 --> 26:51.434
Oh, Jane.

26:51.469 --> 26:52.768
Jacqueline would like to
see you in her office.

26:53.524 --> 26:55.605
She really wants your young moms piece.

27:03.475 --> 27:06.643
<i>So your young mothers piece.</i>

27:07.799 --> 27:10.380
Why are you struggling with it?

27:11.031 --> 27:11.915
I don't know.

27:12.154 --> 27:13.329
I...

27:13.771 --> 27:18.555
I guess I just haven't found an angle
that really works for me yet.

27:21.627 --> 27:24.294
Okay.

27:26.365 --> 27:27.698
It feels too personal.

27:27.733 --> 27:30.333
Jane, if you...

27:30.369 --> 27:32.736
think that you're pregnant
or that you might be...

27:32.771 --> 27:36.440
No. No. It's... it's nothing like that.

27:40.713 --> 27:43.447
Okay, it's a little like that.

27:46.685 --> 27:50.620
I never told you this, but...

27:50.656 --> 27:55.525
I found out that I'm positive
for the BRCA gene mutation.

27:56.562 --> 28:00.397
Oh, Jane, I am so sorry.

28:02.468 --> 28:04.334
I had no idea.

28:05.437 --> 28:08.338
Yeah, I haven't really
told a lot of people.

28:10.609 --> 28:12.542
But the thing is,
is I have a lot of decisions

28:12.578 --> 28:14.578
that I have to make
in the next few years.

28:14.613 --> 28:18.548
Like what kind of preventative
surgery I want to have if any.

28:18.584 --> 28:20.751
And whether or not I want to have kids,

28:20.786 --> 28:23.687
and if I do,
I either need to freeze my eggs

28:23.722 --> 28:26.289
or think about getting pregnant, so...

28:26.325 --> 28:29.292
Well.

28:29.328 --> 28:32.696
That is a lot to handle.

28:32.731 --> 28:35.432
Especially when you're 25.

28:36.335 --> 28:39.336
Yeah.

28:39.371 --> 28:42.372
I don't really know how to
start thinking about it.

28:42.407 --> 28:45.275
Have you talked to your
friends about this?

28:45.310 --> 28:47.377
Yeah.

28:47.412 --> 28:49.546
And, I mean, I know they care,

28:49.581 --> 28:51.615
but they don't really know what to say.

28:54.319 --> 28:56.386
Jane.

28:56.789 --> 29:00.624
I hope you know that I
am always here to talk...

29:00.659 --> 29:03.360
about anything.

29:04.396 --> 29:06.263
Thank you.

29:07.399 --> 29:09.599
And don't worry.

29:09.635 --> 29:13.236
- I'll get the article done.
- Oh.

29:13.272 --> 29:16.540
I am not worried about that.

29:17.609 --> 29:20.302
But if it's tripping you up,
writing about

29:20.346 --> 29:25.415
young 20-somethings who've
chosen to have kids,

29:25.450 --> 29:29.352
then just write about
why you're not ready yet.

29:34.493 --> 29:36.726
Thank you.

29:36.762 --> 29:40.430
I'll think about it.

29:45.504 --> 29:46.469
<i>Right over here, sweetheart.</i>

29:46.505 --> 29:48.405
<i>Look away.</i>

29:48.440 --> 29:50.740
<i>That's it. Beautiful.</i>

29:53.512 --> 29:54.511
Yeah, that lighting is perfect.

29:54.546 --> 29:56.413
It's amazing. I love it.

29:56.448 --> 29:58.582
Go get some more stuff.

30:01.687 --> 30:03.353
Oh, my God.

30:03.388 --> 30:05.322
Looks so good.

30:05.357 --> 30:06.590
Oh, yeah.

30:06.625 --> 30:08.525
- Literally would never know.
- Yay.

30:08.560 --> 30:11.695
Kat, I'm gonna need you to come with me.

30:11.730 --> 30:14.431
Yes.

30:17.636 --> 30:19.569
<i>I use Whole Spa clean wipes</i>

30:19.605 --> 30:22.539
<i>in the middle of the day because
it's a great pick-me-up.</i>

30:22.574 --> 30:26.409
<i>My skin feels soft, hydrated,
and most of all, clean.</i>

30:26.445 --> 30:28.578
<i>It's as if all the
dirt's been wiped away.</i>

30:28.614 --> 30:31.448
<i>Just like how the CEO
of Whole Spa, Eric Miller,</i>

30:31.483 --> 30:33.416
<i>is hoping that having
a queer black woman</i>

30:33.452 --> 30:35.719
<i>featured on their Instagram
story will just wash away</i>

30:35.754 --> 30:39.723
<i>all the bad press he's about to get
for donating to hate groups.</i>

30:42.461 --> 30:43.793
They might try and sue us.

30:43.829 --> 30:46.563
I did everything I was
contractually obligated to do.

30:46.598 --> 30:48.331
I used the cleanser,

30:48.367 --> 30:50.333
listed three things
that I liked about it.

30:50.369 --> 30:52.602
Are these allegations against
the Whole Spa CEO true?

30:52.638 --> 30:54.537
I just spoke with the reporter;

30:54.573 --> 30:57.407
he has multiple sources,
and the story just broke on "Vice."

30:57.442 --> 30:58.642
Did you know about this?

30:58.677 --> 31:00.543
When you agreed to the
product integration?

31:00.579 --> 31:02.379
No, of course not.

31:02.414 --> 31:04.381
But this is still a very
important partnership.

31:04.416 --> 31:09.286
And if we're being honest,
not everyone at Safford is woke.

31:09.321 --> 31:10.620
I mean, Elliot Waxman
from "Porch & Garden"

31:10.656 --> 31:12.555
has been spotted on
more than one occasion

31:12.591 --> 31:15.392
wearing a MAGA hat while golfing.

31:15.427 --> 31:16.626
Well, maybe you should see
if he could do

31:16.662 --> 31:18.561
the next Whole Spa Instagram story.

31:21.333 --> 31:25.368
This is precisely why "Scarlet"
doesn't do advertorials.

31:25.404 --> 31:27.504
It betrays the trust of our readers.

31:27.539 --> 31:29.572
When they pick up an issue of
"Scarlet" magazine,

31:29.608 --> 31:32.742
they expect us to have an
authentic point of view.

31:32.778 --> 31:35.312
I was just trying to
increase our revenue stream.

31:35.347 --> 31:37.414
Well, that's a noble goal.

31:37.449 --> 31:39.683
But neither Kat,
nor "Scarlet" 's integrity

31:39.718 --> 31:42.352
should be up for sale.

31:49.761 --> 31:51.461
- Should we go get a drink?
- Yes.

31:51.496 --> 31:53.730
I wish. I have to go home.

31:53.765 --> 31:55.532
Ben is coming over,
and I'm gonna tell him

31:55.567 --> 31:57.334
what's been going on.

31:57.369 --> 31:58.768
So you know, super fun night.

31:59.566 --> 32:01.738
I'm sorry. But telling Ben is good.

32:01.773 --> 32:03.473
Yeah, he's your boyfriend now.

32:03.508 --> 32:05.275
Which means you get sex on the regular

32:05.310 --> 32:06.643
and he needs to know stuff like this.

32:07.423 --> 32:08.611
Oh, speaking of boyfriends,

32:08.647 --> 32:11.648
I just got an all-caps
happy text from Oliver.

32:11.683 --> 32:13.650
- Wow.
- _

32:13.685 --> 32:16.453
- Followed by an angry one.
- _

32:16.488 --> 32:18.321
Hmm.

32:19.691 --> 32:21.725
Okay, but be forewarned,

32:21.760 --> 32:25.495
S-U-Q is a word,
and I will be playing it.

32:28.600 --> 32:30.700
Um... So, hey.

32:30.736 --> 32:33.536
I have to talk to you about something.

32:33.572 --> 32:34.771
You already apologized
for the other night

32:34.806 --> 32:36.539
and thanked me for the flowers.

32:36.575 --> 32:38.541
I promise you we're good.

32:39.544 --> 32:41.611
It's... it's not about that.

32:43.382 --> 32:45.782
Remember when I told you

32:45.817 --> 32:47.684
how my mom died from breast cancer?

32:50.555 --> 32:52.789
Well, I...

32:52.824 --> 32:57.527
I found out that I'm positive
for the BRCA mutation.

32:59.398 --> 33:01.631
Oh, Jane.

33:04.569 --> 33:06.469
I'm sorry.

33:09.674 --> 33:12.509
Yeah, I...

33:12.544 --> 33:15.345
I found out, like, four months ago,

33:15.380 --> 33:16.679
and I thought that the only thing

33:16.715 --> 33:19.282
I needed to worry about
were the screenings.

33:19.317 --> 33:21.584
But when I saw my doctor the other day

33:21.620 --> 33:23.586
for the side effects, she told me I need

33:23.622 --> 33:25.722
to start thinking about what kind of

33:25.757 --> 33:27.590
preventative measures I wanted to take

33:27.626 --> 33:30.627
and whether or not I want to have kids.

33:32.731 --> 33:35.365
Oh, Jane.

33:37.569 --> 33:39.469
Well.

33:40.472 --> 33:42.405
That's a lot.

33:42.774 --> 33:45.608
The mutation, is it in BRCA1 or BRCA2?

33:45.644 --> 33:47.710
- BRCA1.
- Okay.

33:50.715 --> 33:54.350
And your mother's breast cancer,
was that estrogen sensitive? Because...

33:54.386 --> 33:56.319
Ben.

33:56.354 --> 33:59.389
I need you to act like
my boyfriend right now,

33:59.424 --> 34:01.524
not a doctor.

34:02.427 --> 34:04.260
Yeah, I'm sorry.

34:06.465 --> 34:08.364
You are having regular
mammograms, right?

34:08.400 --> 34:09.527
Yes.

34:09.601 --> 34:11.668
And trans-vaginal ultrasounds
to check for ovarian cancer...

34:11.728 --> 34:14.571
Ben.

34:14.606 --> 34:18.541
I didn't tell you so that you could
give me medical advice.

34:18.577 --> 34:21.311
I told you because...

34:21.346 --> 34:23.379
I want you to know what's been going on.

34:26.318 --> 34:29.385
I'm sorry.
I'm just trying to process this.

34:31.422 --> 34:33.556
I know what this means
in ways other guys don't.

34:33.592 --> 34:35.525
Yeah.

34:37.661 --> 34:40.295
Right now I kind of wish you didn't.

34:45.637 --> 34:48.771
Look, can we just go back
to playing the game,

34:48.806 --> 34:51.373
and just forget I said anything?

34:51.409 --> 34:53.443
Okay?

35:10.498 --> 35:12.276
We tried to pretend
like everything was normal.

35:12.285 --> 35:15.752
But we both knew that it wasn't, so...

35:15.787 --> 35:18.388
I'm sorry, love.

35:20.458 --> 35:22.759
I mean, I don't know
what I expected him to do.

35:22.794 --> 35:28.498
It was cancer, surgery,
potential parenthood,

35:28.533 --> 35:31.768
just wrapped up in one
delightful little package.

35:35.507 --> 35:38.541
Okay, well, let's tackle this
one thing at a time.

35:38.577 --> 35:40.476
You love lists.

35:40.512 --> 35:43.713
And if ever a situation
demanded a pro-con list,

35:43.748 --> 35:47.617
deciding whether or not you
want to have a kid would be it.

35:47.652 --> 35:49.452
I know.

35:51.423 --> 35:52.855
But I don't think I can.

35:52.891 --> 35:56.593
Okay, look, this is probably
the last thing you want to hear,

35:56.628 --> 35:58.394
but I'm the child of two shrinks.

35:58.430 --> 36:01.564
So I think parents are the
root of all of our issues.

36:01.600 --> 36:03.766
Do you think that maybe the reason

36:03.802 --> 36:08.404
you're having trouble picturing yourself
as a mom is because...

36:08.440 --> 36:10.607
you lost yours when you were so young?

36:13.478 --> 36:14.777
Maybe.

36:16.548 --> 36:19.349
I mean...

36:19.384 --> 36:22.552
I only have memories of
my mom when she was sick.

36:24.689 --> 36:26.789
I don't remember anything before that.

36:30.862 --> 36:33.529
And I just keep thinking, like...

36:35.500 --> 36:38.501
Was she the kind of mom who...

36:38.536 --> 36:43.606
got down on the floor and played
with me when I was a kid or...

36:43.642 --> 36:45.775
did my hair...

36:45.810 --> 36:49.646
or read me bedtime
stories and sang to me?

36:52.417 --> 36:55.685
Did she kiss me on the forehead
when she tucked me in at night?

36:58.423 --> 36:59.722
Hey.

36:59.758 --> 37:02.659
Whatever kind of mother she was...

37:02.694 --> 37:06.496
she was amazing...

37:06.531 --> 37:08.598
because so are you.

37:14.606 --> 37:17.807
I just wish that I could talk to her...

37:17.842 --> 37:20.710
and get her advice about all of this.

37:35.827 --> 37:38.561
Looks like the muse has struck.

37:38.596 --> 37:40.830
It looks like it has.

37:42.467 --> 37:44.634
Oh, sorry. It's my brother.

37:47.539 --> 37:49.405
- Hey, Ev.
<i>- Hey, Jane. What's up?</i>

37:49.441 --> 37:50.673
<i>I saw you called.</i>

37:50.709 --> 37:52.709
Yeah, thanks for calling me back.

37:52.744 --> 37:54.577
<i>- Everything okay?</i>
- No, I'm fine.

37:54.612 --> 37:56.813
I just...

37:56.848 --> 38:00.383
- I wanted to ask you about mom.
<i>- What's going on?</i>

38:00.418 --> 38:03.419
Just kind of having trouble remembering.

38:03.455 --> 38:05.421
<i>Like what?</i>

38:05.457 --> 38:07.657
Yeah, like, I mean,

38:07.692 --> 38:10.660
what were bedtimes like?

38:10.695 --> 38:15.598
<i>Well, she used to sing us
that Fleetwood Mac song, "Landslide."</i>

38:15.633 --> 38:17.600
- She did?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

38:18.503 --> 38:20.770
No wonder I love that song.

38:22.373 --> 38:23.573
You wanted to see me?

38:23.608 --> 38:25.641
I wanted to talk to you about Whole Spa.

38:25.677 --> 38:27.577
I should have come to you first.

38:27.612 --> 38:29.345
Cleo should have known better.

38:29.380 --> 38:30.813
I mean, I should have too.

38:30.849 --> 38:35.585
I think I was just so flattered
that they wanted me, I...

38:35.620 --> 38:37.754
I just said yes without thinking, but...

38:37.789 --> 38:40.556
- won't do it again.
- Well, let's not overcorrect.

38:40.592 --> 38:43.760
I mean, you are inspiring.
Your story is powerful,

38:43.795 --> 38:45.762
but don't just let
anybody tell your story.

38:45.797 --> 38:48.531
Find companies and causes
that you feel proud to get behind.

38:48.600 --> 38:50.767
Do you really think I should
try something like that again?

38:50.802 --> 38:53.369
I'd be disappointed if you didn't.

39:05.383 --> 39:11.454
_

39:42.754 --> 39:44.453
Hi, I'm here to pick up

39:44.489 --> 39:45.788
the travel memo for
the fashion department.

39:45.824 --> 39:47.557
And before you ask, yes,

39:47.592 --> 39:49.392
Oliver is booked first class,
aisle seat.

39:49.427 --> 39:50.626
Okay, great.
And Frank's in here too, right?

39:50.662 --> 39:52.762
Of course, and his meal is vegetarian.

39:52.797 --> 39:55.698
And I am holding a middle seat,
back row for you.

39:55.733 --> 39:57.600
Sorry?

39:57.635 --> 39:59.106
It was the only seat left.

39:59.170 --> 40:02.438
Oliver just called this morning.
So it was the best I could do.

40:02.473 --> 40:04.874
But, hey, you're going to Paris, right?

40:06.411 --> 40:07.677
I'm going...

40:07.712 --> 40:09.512
I'm going to Paris for Fashion Week?

40:09.547 --> 40:10.813
Oh, my God.

40:10.849 --> 40:13.382
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

40:14.552 --> 40:16.485
I'm gonna throw up.
I'm not gonna throw up.

40:16.521 --> 40:17.720
Don't throw up.

40:17.755 --> 40:19.655
- I might throw up.
- Don't throw up.

40:19.691 --> 40:22.525
<i>And then she'd read us a bedtime story.</i>

40:22.560 --> 40:25.728
<i>You always wanted
"Harold and the Purple Crayon."</i>

40:30.468 --> 40:31.500
Yeah.

